snippet: As the 125th and last player in the monthlong FedEx Cup playoffs, Ben Crane is golf’s Mr. Irrelevant, but he is embracing his underdog role.
abstract: Ben Crane, the 125th and last golfer in month-long FedEx Cup playoffs is embracing his underdog role; no winner has risen from further down the final regular-season rankings than 19; his odds of winning the Cup, according to Bovada Las Vegas, are 200 to 1.
lead_paragraph: As the 125th and last player in the monthlong FedEx Cup playoffs, Ben Crane is golf’s Mr. Irrelevant, but he is embracing his underdog role.

headline.main: Final Player in Playoff Field Has Some Fun With His Standing
headline.print_headline: Final Player in Playoff Field Has Some Fun With His Standing
